	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind these numbers is a devotion most of the world rarely pauses to honor. The believer who rises before dawn to pray. The discipline of fasting, of charity, of turning the heart toward God again and again through the day. The deep reverence for a God who is supremely great, holy, and merciful — a God to be obeyed and pleased. This is no small thing, and it is worthy of respect.</p><p>And yet, in the quiet, many sincere hearts carry a longing that obedience alone does not fully answer: the longing to be near. To know, not only that God is merciful in general, but that He loves <em>me</em> — personally, tenderly, by name. To stand before Him not only as a servant who hopes he has done enough, but as a child who is held. That longing is not a failure of faith. It may be the very place where God is drawing near to reveal something of Himself He has always wanted you to know.</p>`}
