	aFatherHeading={`A Father for Muslims`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>In the worship you already know, God is great beyond measure — the Creator, the Sovereign, the Merciful, the One before whom all creation bows. All of this is true, and the Father's Heart Bible™ honors every bit of His greatness. But the Scriptures reveal something more, offered here gently for your reflection: this same supremely great God draws near and reveals Himself as a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong>.</p><p>Not a Father in any small or human way — not as a man, and never less than holy — but a Father in tenderness, in nearness, in the love that delights over His own. He does not only command from above; He stoops to gather. He does not only receive the servant who has done enough; He runs to embrace the child who simply comes home.</p><p>This is not offered as an argument to win, but as an invitation to consider: that the God you have sought to please with all your discipline already looks on you with a Father's love, and longs for you to know Him not only as Master, but as the One who calls you His own.</p>`}
