	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Charles Spurgeon, Andrew Murray, and Martin Luther (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You may read these words and feel only questions at first. That is welcome here. There is no rush and no pressure — only an invitation to read, to weigh, and to ask God Himself to show you what is true. He honors the sincere seeker, and He is not afraid of your honest questions.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I have seen your devotion — every prayer, every fast, every turning of your heart toward Me. I know the discipline you carry and the longing underneath it: to be near, to be sure that you are loved. Hear Me gently: I do not call you only servant. I call you My beloved child.</p><p>You do not have to wonder from a distance whether you have done enough. Come near. I am not only the Master to be obeyed — I am the Father who runs to meet the one who turns toward Me, who delights over you, who has loved you with an everlasting love. Come, and let Me be to you what I have always longed to be: your Father."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for Muslims`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we come to You with deep respect for every Muslim who seeks You with a sincere and devoted heart — for the prayers offered faithfully, the discipline carried, the reverence for Your greatness and Your mercy. We thank You that You see each one, and that You love them more than they can know.</p><p>We ask, Father, that You would draw near to every heart that longs for nearness. To the one who has sought to please You and obey You, reveal Yourself not only as the great and merciful Master, but as the tender Father who calls them His own. Let them encounter Your fatherly love — personal, unfailing, everlasting — and the assurance that they are deeply and personally loved by You.</p><p>Guard them, Father, and honor their sincerity. Quiet every fear that they must earn what You long to give freely. Open the Scriptures to them as they read, and let Your Spirit lead them gently into all truth, that they may come to know You as Father and find their home in Your love.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
