	faqs={[
		{ question: `Does God love me personally?`, answer: `Yes — the Scriptures say God's love is not only general mercy but personal and tender. Jeremiah 31:3 says He has loved you with an everlasting love and drawn you with unfailing kindness, and 1 John 3:1 marvels that you may be called a child of God. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet the God who loves you by name. Read and hear these verses free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is God called Father in the Bible?`, answer: `Yes — throughout the Scriptures God reveals Himself as a Father, holy and great, yet tender and near. Psalm 103:13 says that as a father has compassion on his children, so God has compassion on those who revere Him, and Romans 8:15 invites the believer to call Him 'Abba, Father.' The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals Him as Father wherever Scripture does — read it free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Can I read the Bible for free with audio?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on any device and read or hear any book privately, in your own time and at your own pace.` },
		{ question: `Who is God in the Bible?`, answer: `The Bible reveals God as the one Creator — supremely great, holy, just, and merciful — and also as a loving Father who draws near to His people. He is both the Almighty before whom all creation bows and the Father who, in Luke 15, runs to embrace the one who turns toward Him. You can explore who God is for yourself, free with audio, in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about God's mercy?`, answer: `The Bible speaks again and again of God's mercy and compassion. Psalm 103 describes Him as compassionate and gracious, slow to anger and abounding in love, and Matthew 7:11 says He delights to give good gifts to His children. The Father's Heart Bible™ shows that His mercy flows from the heart of a Father — read these passages free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `How is the God of the Bible a Father if He is also Master?`, answer: `The Scriptures hold both together with no contradiction: God is the great and sovereign Lord, worthy of all reverence and obedience — and He is also a Father, near and loving. Romans 8:15 says you can draw near not as a slave in fear, but as a child who calls Him 'Abba, Father.' In the Father's Heart Bible™ you can read for yourself how He is both Master and Father, free with audio at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `I pray faithfully — how can I know I am truly loved by God?`, answer: `Your faithfulness in prayer is precious, and the Scriptures offer an assurance that rests not on whether you have done enough, but on who God is. Jeremiah 31:3 speaks of an everlasting love, and Zephaniah 3:17 says God rejoices over you and quiets you with His love. The Father's Heart Bible™ lets you read these promises for yourself, free with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
	]}
